    "\n",
    "Flatten the images into a 2D data matrix (n x p, where n is the number of samples and p is the number of pixels in each image). Load these and the labels into numpy arrays. Split the data into training (60%) and testing (40%) datasets, stratified on class labels (so that there is an equal percentage of each class type in each of the training and testing sets).\n",
